OSOGBO â€“ Following the hardship inflicted upon residents by fuel subsidy removal by the Federal Government, Governor Ademola Adeleke will soon unveil palliatives to cushion the effects on business and livelihoods. Spokesman to the Governor, Mallam Olawale Rasheed disclosed this while speaking on a radio programme in Osogbo. Rasheed said the planned intervention will cover support for public transport, monitoring of fuel stations and public sector work time reviews. He said top officials are finalising the state palliative plan in line with the directives of Mr Governor.